		<h2>HELPING HANDS<br><u>Constitution</u></h2>

<h4>Article1: Organs of the Association:</h4>
a) The association shall function through the following organs:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;i) The General Body,<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;ii) The Executive Committee,<br>
b) The tenure of office of all the elected organs shall be one year.
<h4>Article 2: The General Body:</h4>
The General Body shall consist of all the students of RGUKT. It shall consider the Annual
Report and the budget presented by the Executive Committee during annual day submitted
by the Finance Dept and review, the activities of the Association for the purpose of
formulating a programme of action for the ensuing year. Helping hands class
representatives also a part of general body but they have chance to be get elected an EC
member.
<h4>Article 3: The Executive Committee:</h4>
The Executive committee shall consist of:
<ul type="circle">
 <li> A President (Faculty Member)</li>
<li>A Vice-President (E3 Student)</li>
<li> A General Secretary (Faculty Member)</li>
<li>Four Joint Secretaries (Faculty Member or Student member)</li>
<li> A Treasurer (Faculty Member)</li>
<li>Joint Treasurer (E3 Student)</li>
<li> Executive members</li>
</ul>
<h4>Article 4: Structure of Executive Committee</h4>
<center><img src="Docs/5.png"></img></center>

<h4>Article 5: Powers and Functions of the Members of the Executive Committee:</h4>
The Executive authority of the association shall be vested in the Executive Committee. The
Executive Committee <b>with 2/3rd of majority will decide the any matters.</b> The committee
shall also have the power to make necessary rules and regulations subject to the provisions
of this constitution.

<b>i) The President:</b> He/ She shall preside over the meetings of the Executive
  Committee and General Body and shall exercise general supervision over
 the Association in the formulation of its policies and programmes and for
coordination of its activities.<br><br/>
<b>ii) The Vice President:</b> He/ She shall assist the President in the discharge of
   his functions. In the absence of the president or in the case of the office of
  the president falling vacant for any reason, the Executive committee shall
 nominate Vice-President to officiate as President.<br><br/>
<b>iii) The General Secretary:</b> He/ She shall in consultation with the President
    convene the meetings of the Executive committee, and The General Body
   and shall maintain the minutes of those meetings. He/ She shall be in-charge
  of all the Correspondence and records of the Association and shall be
 responsible for their safe custody. He/ She shall also perform such other
duties and functions as may be assigned to him by the Executive committee,
and the general Body.<br><b>
[Every month GS will conduct the meeting with JS of all the dept in
presence of president and JS will hand over the every month details
about finance and activity to GS, copy of details need to give Web Dept
for necessary action after completion of president sign]</b><br><br/>
<b>iv) The Joint Secretaries: </b>They shall assist the General Secretary in the
   discharge of his functions. In the event of absence of General Secretary or of
  the office of General Secretary falling vacant for any reason, The Executive
 Committee shall nominate one of the Joint Secretaries to officiate as the
General Secretary with 2/3rd majority of Executive Committee<br><br/>
<b>v) The Treasurer: </b>He/ She shall maintain the accounts of the association and
  submit them to the Executive Committee from time to time. He/ She shall
 deposit all the amounts accruing to the Association in a Nationalized Bank
approved by the Executive Committee. All the withdrawals from the Bank
shall be made under the joint signatures of any two of the President or
Vice president and Treasurer or Joint Treasurers. Ensure that minimum
one faculty member and one student should be there.<br><br>

<b>vi) Joint Treasurers:</b> He/ She shall assist the Treasurer in the discharge of
   his/her functions. In the event of absence of Treasurer or of the office of
  Treasurer falling vacant for any reason, the Executive committee shall
 nominate Joint Treasurers to officiate as the Treasurer.<br><br/>

<h4>Article 6: Mode of Elections:</h4>
<h4>Faculty Executive Committee (EC) members:</h4>
Interested faculty who wish to be EC member of HH can apply through RGUKT, Nuzvid
online HH portal. Minimum one year experience is required to become EC member. After
immediate join, initial one year these faculty will participate in different activities
organized by HH, based on ability, performance and attendance in meetings in one year
they are considered for being EC member.<br>

		<center><img src="Docs/1.png"></img></center>

<h4>Student members:</h4>
There are three levels of student categories are members in HH.<br>
1. Helping Hands Representatives (HR) members<br>
2. Branch Representatives (BR) for E2, E3 & E4 / Class Representatives (CR) for
PUC1, PUC2 & E1 members<br>
3. Executive Committee (EC) members<br>
4. Supporting Team<br>

<h3>1. Helping Hands Representatives (HR) members:</h3>
Selection process for HR members can be done for the classes PUC1, PUC2, E1 & E2
based on 2min oral representation on particular topic in their respective classes. These
process should be done in night study hours (Monday-Thursday) and maximum of three
day with proper permission from President and General secretory of HH committee.
<br><br><center><img src="2.png"></center></src>
<h3>2.Branch Representatives/ Cluster Representatives (B.R/C.R):</h3>
<br><center><img src="3.png"></img></center><br>

Interested candidate from the HR of PUC -1, PUC -2, E-1 and E-2 will be participate.<br>
PUC-1: Based on 10 marks objective exam (paper will be based HH constitution and
works)<br>
PUC-2: Based on 10 marks objective exam (paper will be based HH constitution and
works)<br>
E-1
: Based on 10 marks objective exam (paper will be based HH constitution and works)
+ Interview by E4 EC members (10marks)<br>
E-2
: Based on 10 marks objective and written exam (paper will be based HH
constitution and works)<br>
+ Interview by E4 EC members (10marks)

<h4>3.EC members:</h4>
	<br><center><img src="4.png"></img></center><br>
For PUC -1, PUC -2 and E1 EC members there will be an interview (10marks) only and it
will be conducted by GS and JS.<br>
For E2 EC members there will be a written test of objective (10marks) and descriptive
(5marks) + group discussion (15marks) + Interview (20 marks) and it will be conducted by
President, GS and JS. Weightage will be given for the students who are continuously
working with HH at any level.
<h4>4.Supporting Team:</h4>
There will not be any procedure for selection of supporting team. Interested Students from
general body can be a part of supporting team. They have no rights to be part of any
decision making. But there will be a highest chance for supporting students to be an EC
member based on the performance throughout the year and by passing through proper
election process.
Supporting team are maximum of 6 student members will be from each department. Among
that 1 or 2 members are assigned for financial department.<br>
<b>*Note:</b> If any student wants to relieve from HH committee needs to keep a request letter for
replacement of eligible candidate from respective department/cluster to HH.

<h4>Article 7: Amendment of the Constitution:</h4>
i) The Executive Committee member may propose amendments to any provision of
this constitution and the amendment to the constitution shall be affected by a vote of
2/3rd majority of Executive committee members.<br>
ii) The amendments to the constitution may also be proposed by any member in
writing specifying the reasons and the text of proposed amendment along with the
signature of at least fifty members of the general body, and communicated to the
respective Joint Secretary. The concern Joint Secretary shall forthwith place the
proposed amendment before the Executive committee in consult with General
Secretary. The amendment to the constitution shall be affected by a vote of 2/3 rd
majority of executive committee members.




